lead_paragraph: Russell Westbrook scored a team-high 42 points, including 11 consecutive in the final five minutes, and reserve guard Alex Abrines scored 18 points to lift the Oklahoma City Thunder to a 121-110 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Wednesday at the Smoothie King Center.

headline.main: Westbrook Pours in 42 Points to Lead Thunder Past Pelicans
headline.print_headline: Westbrook Pours in 42 Points to Lead Thunder Past Pelicans
